The Telegraph - Calcutta : Opinion
		 Monday, September 23, 2002 				 Heritage garden and tourist hotspot
								Arati Patodia: Mysore Garden has turned out to be a perfect spot. Can steps be taken to make it one of the tourist attractions of the city?																																																													Mysore Garden is 107 years old and plans are afoot to declare it a heritage park. If the state government wishes, it can be turned into an important tourist spot. The garden is thrown open to the public from 6-8 am and 5-8 pm in summer and from 4.30 pm to 7.30 pm during winter.
